This is the README for HTML::Make::Page version 0.02.

HTML::Make::Page is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language,
a library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document
contains four sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

HTML::Make::Page - Automate making HTML <head> and <body>

This module simplifies generating the <head> and <body> elements of an
HTML page using "HTML::Make".

Restrictions

The output is restricted to the following variants of HTML:

HTML 5 only

The output has a doctype of "< <!DOCTYPE html" >>.

Lower-case tags only

No <HTML> etc., the tags generated are lower-case only.

UTF-8 encoding only

The output has "< <meta charset='UTF-8'" >> added automatically.

Viewport is added automatically

The viewport meta element, necessary for viewing web pages on mobile
phones, is automatically added to the output.

XHTML tags are not supported

XHTML tags of the form "< <br/" >> are not necessary in HTML 5 and
are not supported.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following
website:

    * http://metacpan.org/release/HTML-Make-Page

(This link goes to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your
computer using

    perldoc HTML::Make::Page

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

This module requires Perl version 5.6.1 or later.

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan HTML::Make::Page

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm HTML::Make::Page

To install the module from the source file, HTML-Make-Page-0.02.tar.gz,
follow this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz HTML-Make-Page-0.02.tar.gz
    cd HTML-Make-Page-0.02
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can
report a bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/html-make-page/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of HTML::Make::Page, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/html-make-page>. 

